CSS

.bg-gray {
    padding: 20px;
    background: #f9f9f9;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.bg-gray h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
}

.gray-wrapper {
    background: #f9f9f9;
}

.row-wide>.col-md-12[class*="section"] {
    padding: 0;
}

HTML

1. For any content item that needs a gray background add in 'bg-gray' within the CSS Wrapper Class Name Field
2. If multiple items within one row need seperate gray backgrounds, add in 'row-wide' along with 'bg-gray'
